---
description: Local development, Docker images, Kubernetes manifests, and CI/CD flows
---

# Local development

- Requirements: Node 24.14+, PNPM 10+, MySQL 8, Redis
- Environment: copy .env.example → .env (do not commit .env)
- Start services: docker compose up -d (mysql on 3309, redis on 6380 by default)
- Generate Prisma client: pnpm --filter dineros-app exec prisma generate
- Run dev server: pnpm dev (from repo root or filter to dineros-app)

Devcontainer (.devcontainer/docker-compose.yml)
- Provides MySQL and Redis alongside a Node dev container, pre-wiring DATABASE_URL and Redis host/port for convenience

# Docker images

App (app/Dockerfile)
- Multi-stage pnpm + Prisma generate + nuxt build → slim runner
- Exposes PORT (default 3000, set to 80 in K8S). Copies .output and prisma directory

Microservice (microservice/Dockerfile)
- Multi-stage with pnpm + Prisma generate
- Runtime image supports NODE_ENV=test branch (test-start) vs start; includes a separate target runner-keyrotate for staging CronJob that bundles kubectl + curl + jq and a k8s-rotate-db-key.sh script

# Kubernetes manifests

- .deploy/dineros.template.yaml renders two Deployments (app and microservice), Services, and Ingress
- Environment sources:
  - DATABASE_URL from per-service secrets (SECRET_DATABASE_MAIN, SECRET_DATABASE_MICRO)
  - DB field encryption material from SECRET_DB (DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY and decryption keys)
  - App secrets from SECRET_APP (Plaid, Postmark, INTERNAL_API_TOKEN, etc.)
  - JWT secret from SECRET_JWT (DINEROS_JWT_SECRET)
- Readiness/liveness/startup probes hit /health/ready and /health/live
- App talks to microservice via MICROSERVICE_INTERNAL_URL ClusterIP service
- Redis hostname is a cluster Redis (redis-master.redis.svc.cluster.local) in templates; local dev uses docker-compose redis

Staging key rotation
- .deploy/key-rotation-cronjob.template.yaml runs nightly; uses microservice :keyrotate image and a RBAC Role/RoleBinding in .deploy/key-rotation-rbac.template.yaml
- Cron executes microservice/scripts/k8s-rotate-db-key.sh which patches the DB key secret, rolls Deployments, and calls microservice migrate endpoint

# CI/CD (GitHub Actions)

PR checks (.github/workflows/pr.yml)
- Jobs: lint, test (Vitest with minimal env), pre-commit security (TruffleHog + hooks), CodeQL
- If PR originates from same repo, builds app and microservice images (tags pr-<N>-<SHA>) and deploys to staging via .github/actions/deploy-dineros-gke/action.yml, then verifies rollout and public /health/ready
- Optionally posts a Bugbot trigger comment (Cursor integration)

Default branch deploy (.github/workflows/main.yml)
- On push to main/master: build app and microservice, push to GCR, then deploy production with envsubst-rendered .deploy templates
- Post-deploy verification hits production health endpoints via verify script

Code scanning and quality
- CodeQL scheduled weekly (codeql.yml)
- SonarQube scan available as workflow-dispatch (sonar.yml) with coverage from pnpm test:coverage

# Secrets and env

- Keep DATABASE_URL out of SECRET_DB; SECRET_DB only contains field-encryption material (per comments in templates)
- server/envSchema.ts validates runtime env. Update it when adding new variables
- AGENTS.md notes Cursor Cloud env overrides (export DATABASE_URL locally when an injected remote URL may exist)
